------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Objective

The objective of this exercise is to develop a deeper understanding of Object-Oriented Programming (OOP) by:

Using lists as class attributes
Adding and managing elements dynamically within a class
Creating methods that modify and display object data
Modeling a real-world scenario (course enrollment) using classes and objects
This exercise reinforces the concepts of classes, attributes, methods, and data structures in OOP.

Instructions

Create a class called Course with the attributes name and students (which is an empty list at the beginning).
Add the following methods:
add_student() that takes a studentâ€™s name and adds it to the list.
display_students() that displays the list of enrolled students.
Create an object of the Course class, add several students, then display the list of enrolled students.
